        "content": "<p>It seems that the hack can be simplified to <code>simp [show (1 + 1 : Fin 4) = 2 from rfl]</code><br>\nThe second solution doesn't work for me because it uses <code>Fin</code> only, which doesn't support casting from a <code>Nat</code>, as opposed to <code>ZMod</code>.<br>\nWhy is Lean okay with doing arithmetic on <code>Fin</code> and then lifting it to <code>ZMod</code>, but it isn't capable of doing that arithmetic in <code>simp</code> without help?</p>",
